Description: "Angry Birds Breakfast 1" is a breakfast-themed mobile game featuring the iconic Angry Birds characters flinging breakfast foods to defeat green pigs and rescue stolen eggs.

"Angry Birds Classic" is the groundbreaking and much-loved mobile game that revolutionized the gaming industry. Developed by Rovio Entertainment, it was first released in December 2009 and quickly became a global sensation. In this addictively fun game, players are tasked with launching a variety of cute and colorful birds from a slingshot to dismantle intricate structures housing pesky green pigs.

"Angry Birds Rio" is an exciting installment in the popular Angry Birds franchise, developed by Rovio Entertainment in partnership with 20th Century Fox. Released in March 2011, the game was inspired by the animated film "Rio." In this edition, the Angry Birds are not battling against the usual green pigs but instead find themselves in the vibrant city of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.

"Angry Birds Seasons" is a captivating spin-off of the popular Angry Birds franchise, developed by Rovio Entertainment. Released in October 2010, the game introduces a seasonal theme, with each level pack corresponding to various holidays and events throughout the year.

"Angry Birds Space" is a captivating and innovative addition to the beloved Angry Birds franchise, developed by Rovio Entertainment. Released in March 2012, the game takes the classic bird-flinging gameplay to new heights by introducing players to a whole new dimension of physics-based puzzles.

"Angry Birds Star Wars" is an epic crossover between the world-famous Angry Birds franchise and the iconic "Star Wars" universe. Developed by Rovio Entertainment in collaboration with Lucasfilm, the game was launched in November 2012 and quickly became a massive hit.

"Angry Birds Star Wars II" is a thrilling sequel to the successful crossover between the Angry Birds franchise and the legendary "Star Wars" universe. Developed by Rovio Entertainment in partnership with Lucasfilm, the game was released in September 2013.

"Bad Piggies" is a spin-off game from the Angry Birds franchise, created by Rovio Entertainment. Released in September 2012, the game takes a unique perspective by allowing players to take on the role of the mischievous green pigs, who are typically the antagonists in the Angry Birds series.

"Legacy of Flan: Flan Rising" is an interesting RPG with a unique fighting and leveling system. You play a group of four flans (little marshmallow-like creatures), which all have different strengths and weaknesses. While fighting enemies you can collect drops that change one flan into a new one with new abilities. This way your group will get stronger and be able to fight more powerful foes. But it's not always easy to find the right combination of flans to win a fight. Made by Scott Cawthon in 2003.

"The Desolate Room" is a retro-style indie game developed by Scott Cawthon, the creator of the popular "Five Nights at Freddy's" series. It was released in 2007 and serves as one of Scott's earlier works in game development.
